content.description: Start in a crack and move right onto the face to the first bolt. Climb the slab-ish final face to anchors. Steve said that the bolts are kinda in weird spots so be aware of this.
content.location: Farthest left route on the wall

content.description: Follow crimps and rails up to a small roof with a bomber hand jam and prepare for the finishing sequence.
content.location: This route is the second line from the right

climbs.name: Mercury Rising
climbs.fa: Anders Zway, Chris May, Brian Grisham

content.description: This line starts in a small shallow flaring crack and moves out a small overhang. Pull on some jugs and prepare for the tough committing crux. Leave some juice for getting to the chains, you'll need it.

This line fallows the main crack that shoots diagonally left across the main part of the wall. Interesting climbing and good gear.  

  This route finishes on the same anchors as Before The Fall 

  There is some loose stuff here and there, so if you go out there don't be afraid to clean a little while your at it.
content.protection: Small to Medium Nuts. Singles from a Blue TCU to #3 cam should be plenty. Anchors.

climbs.name: H1N1
climbs.fa: Anders Zway, Dominic Weinstock, Brian G.

content.description: Start in crack and move up and over a bulge. Make some burly moves and gun for a good rest. The final moves can be tricky, so stay tight to the end.

climbs.name: Fear The Fighter
climbs.fa: Dominic Weinstock, Anders Zway, Chris May

content.description:
Start on some very burly moves through a right running crack. Some very camouflaged crimps are key to make the moves easier. A tricky hard to read section guards the middle of this route.   

  (Note: the second bolt can be hard to clip. Bring a stick clip if you concerned)
A nice steep line going up the center of the wall. This route is sustained and has a crux in the middle of the route.
content.location: Center of the wall. Right of Fear The Fighter.

content.description: A great little area with steep climbing on some decent desert rock. The wall faces east so it get morning sun and goes into the shade around 1.
